steps.apply:
Start: {S' -> .S}
Dot before S, so add S-rules:
  S -> .<L>
Dot before <, no non-terminal, stop for S.
Now I_0 = {
  S' -> .S,
  S -> .<L>
}

Items in I_0 with dot before '<':
  S -> .<L> => after reading <: S -> <.L>

Kernel = {S -> <.L>}

FIRST(daT) = {d}
FIRST(Rf) = FIRST(R) = {c, d}  (since R -> caTR | d)
FIRST(aS) = {a}
FIRST(bT) = {b}
FIRST(c) = {c}
FIRST(caTR) = {c}
FIRST(d) = {d}

Note: FIRST(S) = {d, c}  (from daT and Rf)
FIRST(T) = {a, b, c}
FIRST(R) = {c, d}
